    <title>Strawberry Ice Cream Recipe</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/recipestyle.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Strawberry Ice Cream</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups fresh strawberries, hulled and sliced</li>
            <li>1 cup granulated sugar</li>
            <li>2 cups heavy cream</li>
            <li>1 cup whole milk</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>icecream</li>
            <li>dessert</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a blender, puree the fresh strawberries with half of the sugar until smooth.</li>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine the strawberry puree, remaining sugar, heavy cream, whole milk, and vanilla extract. Mix until the sugar is dissolved.</li>
            <li>Transfer the mixture to an ice cream maker and churn according to the manufacturer's instructions until it reaches a soft-serve consistency.</li>
            <li>If desired, fold in additional sliced strawberries for texture.</li>
            <li>Transfer the churned ice cream to a lidded container and freeze for at least 4 hours or until firm.</li>
            <li>Scoop and serve your refreshing Strawberry Ice Cream!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
